g.text: WEB 1:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Let's start with Web1, also known as the Read-Only Web.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This phase began in the early 1990s and lasted till the early 2000s.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Back then, websites were static mostly built using plain HTML. There was no interactivity. You couldnt log in, comment, or create content.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Users were simply readers, and content was created by a small group of developers or organizations.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Think of it like an online newspaper you could only read what was published, nothing more.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Popular examples from this era include Wikipedia.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In short Web1 was about consuming information, not interacting with it."

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: WEB2:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "After Web1 came Web2, often called the Read and Write Web.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: It started around the early 2000s and is what most of us are familiar with today.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web2, users are not just consumers of content theyre also creators.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Thanks to platforms like Facebook, YouTube, Twitter, and Instagram, anyone can post, comment, like, share, or go live.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Web2 introduced dynamic content, user logins, real-time updates, and personalized experiences.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But heres the catch centralized companies own and control your data. You use their platform, and they monetize your information.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: So, while Web2 gave us a voice, it came with a cost privacy and data control."

g.text: WEB3:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Lets talk about Web3, the newest phase of the internet also called the Read, Write, and Own Web.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web1, you could only read information.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web2, you could read and write like posting photos or commenting.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But in Web3, you can read, write, and also own things on the internet.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Web3 is built using a special technology called blockchain. Think of it like a notebook that everyone can see, no one can erase, and everyone agrees it is

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: true. In Web3, you dont need to sign up with your email. Instead, you use something called a crypto wallet like a digital ID that lets you use apps and

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: also store money or items online.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You can own digital stuff like coins, artwork, or even game items and no one can take them from you, not even the platform.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Also, Web3 doesnt depend on big companies like Google or Facebook to run things. Its decentralized, meaning its shared among many computers, and no

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: single person or company is the boss.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In short, Web3 gives you more control, more privacy, and real ownership of your online life."

g.text: Encryption:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Lets talk about encryption its like putting your message or data in a locked box so that only the right person can open it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: When you send something on the internet like a message, password, or payment it travels through many servers and networks. Without protection,

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: anyone could see or steal it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Thats where encryption comes in. It takes your data and scrambles it into a secret code. If someone tries to read it without the key, it looks like

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: complete nonsense.+

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Only the person who has the right key can unlock it and read the real message.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: For example:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: If you text your friend, encryption makes sure only your friend can read it, not hackers or even the app company.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web3, encryption is very important because it helps protect your wallet, your identity, and your money.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: So, in simple words encryption keeps your digital stuff safe and private."

g.text: Hashing :

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Now lets talk about hashing its like creating a digital fingerprint of any data.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Heres how it works:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: When you put any message, file, or password through a hashing function, it turns it into a fixed-length code like a short, unique string of letters and

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: numbers.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Even a small change in the original data creates a completely different hash.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Example:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: If you hash the word Hello, you might get something like 5d41402abc...

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But if you change it to hello with a lowercase h, the hash becomes totally different.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Here are some important points:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its one-way you cant reverse a hash to get the original data.

Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its used to check integrity to see if something has been changed.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its also used in storing passwords, blockchain security, and verifying data.

g.text: In Web3 and blockchain, hashing helps keep data secure, tamper-proof, and trustworthy just like sealing something with a fingerprint that no one can

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: fake."

g.text: ZK:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Lets understand something really cool in Web3 called ZK, short for Zero-Knowledge Proofs.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Imagine this:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You want to prove something is true without showing the actual information.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Sounds strange, right? But heres a simple example:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Lets say you want to prove youre over 18 to enter a website but you dont want to show your exact age or your ID.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: With Zero-Knowledge Proofs, you can prove that youre over 18 without revealing anything else.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In simple words

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You prove that you know something, without revealing the secret itself.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web3, ZK is used to:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Prove identity without sharing personal data

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Make transactions private and secure

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Verify something is correct without exposing details

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its a smart way to protect your privacy, while still building trust."

g.text: Blockchain:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Lets break down Blockchain the core technology behind Web3.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Imagine a notebook that anyone can see, but no one can secretly change.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This notebook records information in blocks like pages.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Each block contains data, like transactions or records, and is linked to the previous one forming a chain of blocks. Thats why its called a blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Heres what makes it special:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Decentralized Its not stored in one place or controlled by one company. Its shared across many computers around the world.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Secure Once something is written in a block, no one can change it without everyone's agreement.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Transparent Everyone can see whats inside the blockchain. Its open and public.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: For example, when you send crypto to someone, that transaction is added to a block and permanently recorded no middleman needed.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In short

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Blockchain is like a digital record book thats public, unchangeable, and doesnt need anyones permission."

g.text: Ledger:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A ledger is just a record book a place where you keep track of things like who paid what, who owns what, or what happened when.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In old times, businesses used physical books to write all this down.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In todays digital world, ledgers are stored on computers.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Now, in Web3 and blockchain, we use something called a distributed ledger. Heres what that means:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: It records every transaction or activity.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its shared across many computers, not just one so no single person controls it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its secure once a record is added, it cant be changed without everyone knowing.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: So when you hear ledger in Web3, just think:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its a secure, shared record book that keeps track of everything on the blockchain and everyone can trust whats written in it.

g.text: Wallets:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "Now lets talk about wallets one of the most important tools in Web3.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A wallet is like your digital pocket for the blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But unlike a physical wallet, it doesnt actually store money or coins. Instead, it stores your keys which let you access your account and control your

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: digital assets.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Every wallet has:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A public key (or wallet address) like your username. You can share it with others to receive crypto or NFTs.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A private key like your secret password. It proves that you own your account. Never share this with anyone.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: There are two main types of wallets:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Hot Wallets connected to the internet (like MetaMask or Trust Wallet). Easy to use, but less secure.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Cold Wallets offline (like Ledger or Trezor). Very secure, good for storing large amounts.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web3, your wallet is your identity, your bank, and your passport all in one.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You use it to log into dApps, send crypto, buy NFTs, and more without needing a central company to manage your account."

g.text: Seed Phrase, Private Key, Public Key:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: "When you create a wallet in Web3, three important things are generated your public key, private key, and seed phrase.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Lets break them down in simple terms:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 1. Private Key Your Master Password

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Think of the private key as your secret digital signature.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: It proves you own your wallet and gives you the power to send crypto or interact with the blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: If someone gets your private key, they can take everything.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: If you lose it, you lose access forever.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Never share it. Never lose it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 2. Public Key Your Blockchain Username

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The public key is like your username or wallet address.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its safe to share this is how others send you crypto, NFTs, or messages.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its created from the private key but cant be used to guess the private key back.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Public = Safe to share

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Private = Keep it secret

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 3. Seed Phrase Your Backup Key

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The seed phrase (also called recovery phrase) is a list of 12 or 24 words.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its a human-readable version of your private key.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: It can fully restore your wallet so if you lose your phone or device, you can recover everything using this phrase.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Anyone with your seed phrase can steal all your assets.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: So think of it this way:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Public Key = Your address

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Private Key = Your password

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Phrase = Your backup password

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Web3, you are your wallet.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: No password resets, no customer support youre in full control, and with that comes full responsibility."

g.text: "Lets dive into one of the most important tools in Web3 the wallet.

g.text: A wallet in Web3 is your digital identity. It lets you access the blockchain, send and receive crypto, and interact with decentralized apps also called

g.text: "Lets talk about Networks in Web3 theyre the backbone of everything that happens on the blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A network is a group of computers (or nodes) that work together to run a blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: These computers:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Validate transactions

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Add new blocks to the chain

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Keep the system secure and decentralized

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Each network has its own rules, coins, and ecosystem.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Every Web3 action sending crypto, minting NFTs, using dApps happens on a specific network.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: So when you connect your wallet, you must choose the right network to match the blockchain you're working with.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Important things to remember

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A network is where the blockchain lives and operates.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Different blockchains means different networks.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Your wallet must connect to the right network to interact properly.

g.text: MultiSig Wallet:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A multisignature wallet is a type of crypto wallet that requires more than one private key to approve a transaction.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Instead of a single person having full control, multiple parties share control over the wallet.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: How it works (Basic Example)

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You can take example of a bank locker

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You need 2 out of 3 keys to open it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: If you only have 1 key, you cant access the locker.

g.text: Now lets talk about TestNet

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A Testnet is a testing version of a blockchain network.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: It looks and works just like the real thing but the coins on it have no real value.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Developers use testnets to:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Experiment with new features

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Find bugs without losing real money

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The Mainnet is the real, live blockchain network.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This is where:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Transactions use real money (like ETH, MATIC, BNB)

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Everything is permanent and public

Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Once your project works fine on Testnet, you can deploy it to Mainnet where real users can interact with it.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Mainnet = Real money, real impact

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Important: Before you go live on Mainnet always test on Testnet!"

g.text: "Now lets talk about dApps, short for Decentralized Applications.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Youve probably used apps like Instagram, WhatsApp, or Google Docs these are called centralized apps. Theyre owned and controlled by companies that

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: store all your data on their private servers.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But in Web3, we have dApps Decentralized Applications.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A dApp is an application that runs on a blockchain network instead of centralized servers.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: That means:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Theres no single company controlling it

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Its powered by smart contracts

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Your data stays with you, not with a big tech company

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You interact with dApps using your wallet, not your email or password.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Now lets talk about how dApps Work:

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The frontend (what you see) is similar to normal apps a website or interface

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: But the backend runs on smart contracts on the blockchain

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Every action you take (like swapping tokens, buying an NFT, or voting in a DAO) is handled by the blockchain in a transparent, secure, and automated way

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Web3 wallets are used in DApps for interacting with the blockchain.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In Summary:

g.text: dApps are not just one thing they come in many types.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Some manage money, others let you play games, vote, create art, or own your identity.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
